# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
# Jyzrox — Environment Configuration
# Copy to .env and edit values.  Lines starting with # are comments.
# ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

# ── General ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
TZ=Asia/Taipei
PUID=1042
PGID=1042

# ── Nginx ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
HTTP_PORT=35689
NGINX_CLIENT_MAX_BODY_SIZE=100m

# ── PostgreSQL ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
POSTGRES_DB=vault
POSTGRES_USER=vault
POSTGRES_PASSWORD=changeme_strong_password
# DATABASE_URL is auto-composed from the above — no need to set manually.

# ── Redis ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
REDIS_URL=redis://redis:6379
REDIS_MAXMEMORY=768mb

# ── Security ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# AES-256-GCM key for credential encryption (exactly 32 bytes, base64)
# Generate: python3 -c "import secrets,base64; print(base64.b64encode(secrets.token_bytes(32)).decode())"
CREDENTIAL_ENCRYPT_KEY=CHANGE_ME_GENERATE_WITH_COMMAND_ABOVE

# ── E-Hentai ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
EH_MAX_CONCURRENCY=2
EH_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=30
EH_ACQUIRE_TIMEOUT=60
EH_DOWNLOAD_CONCURRENCY=3
EH_DOWNLOAD_MAX_RETRIES=3

# ── Pixiv ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
PIXIV_MAX_CONCURRENCY=4
PIXIV_IMAGE_CONCURRENCY=6
PIXIV_REQUEST_TIMEOUT=30

# ── Download & Storage ────────────────────────────────────────────────
DISK_MIN_FREE_GB=2.0

# ── Library ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
LIBRARY_SCAN_INTERVAL_HOURS=24
WATCHER_POLLING_INTERVAL=60

# ── Rate Limiting ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
RATE_LIMIT_LOGIN=5
RATE_LIMIT_WINDOW=300

# ── AI Tagger (optional, needs: docker compose --profile tagging) ─────
TAG_MODEL_ENABLED=false
TAG_MODEL_NAME=SmilingWolf/wd-swinv2-tagger-v3
TAG_GENERAL_THRESHOLD=0.35
TAG_CHARACTER_THRESHOLD=0.85
TAGGER_URL=http://tagger:8100
TAGGER_TIMEOUT=30

# Inference backend — uncomment ONE line below, keep the rest commented:
ONNX_PROVIDERS=CPUExecutionProvider
# ONNX_PROVIDERS=CUDAExecutionProvider                          # NVIDIA GPU
# ONNX_PROVIDERS=CUDAExecutionProvider,CPUExecutionProvider     # NVIDIA GPU + CPU fallback
# ONNX_PROVIDERS=TensorrtExecutionProvider                      # NVIDIA TensorRT (fastest)
# ONNX_PROVIDERS=OpenVINOExecutionProvider                      # Intel GPU / NPU
# ONNX_PROVIDERS=CoreMLExecutionProvider                        # macOS Apple Silicon
#
# NOTE: GPU providers require matching runtime libraries in the tagger image.
#   CUDA / TensorRT  → replace onnxruntime with onnxruntime-gpu in tagger/requirements.txt
#                       and use an NVIDIA CUDA base image in tagger/Dockerfile.
#   OpenVINO          → pip install onnxruntime-openvino
